        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-22 21:02:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n(4 comments)\n\nWhile several of these checks are already present in other tests in sanity-PFL, it is a good idea to have at least a few PFL-related subtests in sanity.sh so that they are exercised in \"trivial\" test runs,  so I'm not against them being here. It seems possible that all of these checks could be done with the files from a single set of directories, rather than creating and deleting them once for each subtest?\n\nThe descriptions of the various checks could be improved a bit, or just removed, since \"should return 15 files\" isn't very useful in itself.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
